1	Use Case [#]:  [Add New Service]
1.1	Description
The Admin wants to add a new service to the service catalogue 

1.2	Level
High level 

1.3	Trigger
The Admin clicks the add new service button 

1.4	Primary Actor
The Admin 

1.5	Additional/Supporting Actors
The Customer
Database 

1.6	Stakeholders 
•	Employees
•	Order system
•	Shipping 

1.7	Preconditions

The Admin must have logged in as an admin to the company website open in the browser.
The Admin must have clicked on the add new service button.

1.8	Main Success Scenario
1.	Admin clicks on the add new service button.
2.	Admin inputs information about the new service.
3.	Database registers new service.
4.	Admin confirms the details of new Service.
5.	The system confirms registration of new service.
6.	The system adds new service on the site.

1.9	Extensions
1.	Exception: Submitted data is incomplete:
1.	System displays a warning message
2.	Admin enters additional data.
3.	The System responds.

1.	Alternative: Admin inputs required data.
1.	System confirms information.
2.	System processes data.
3.	System sends confirmation.

1.10	Post Conditions

1.10.1	Success End Condition
The Admin receives confirmation. 
The service is present online for customers and employees to view and select.

1.10.2	Minimal Guarantees
The admin receives confirmation on the additional service added. The system logs the new service and updates the admin request history in the service inventory.

1.10.3	Failure End Condition
The Company’s Service inventory remains unchanged.

1.11	Frequency
Depends of the success of the business.

1.12	Special Requirements
[Describe any additional factors that impact the execution of the use case. These could be environmental, regulatory, organizational or market-driven in nature.]

1.12.1	Performance
The Admin should be taken to the service confirmation screen soon after they have confirmed that their input information was correct.

1.12.2	Security
The Admin should have successfully logged into the admin account to access services changes. 

1.12.3	Usability / Accessibility
Admin must be able to view page in English.

1.12.4	Other

1.13	Issues and Next Steps

